n their decisions. IE a cleric might be given 2-3 times as much as a magician because their equip effects the guild more. For many, a guild is more of a hassle than a boon. Some guilds have required levels just to tag along, then must be recommended + AAs to join, and don't forget that you must solidly raid for 3 months to join. That gets you in-- then youre in for it if the officers are total idiots. I recall a member of a bad guild on this server telling me that their leader had threatened virtually every member of the guild for something or another. When the server was new(this is kane bayle), a member was kicked from them for having stood in front of Venril Sathir who was not tanking. Imo killing VS with mroe than 7 people is a joke, taking 50 is ridiculous, kicking someone for being unenlightened is awful(moved after told), but they also wiped!<br><br>Fortunately I am a guild with a smarter/nicer leadership that does their job well. Guilds vary and are different. Find one that suits you. If you want a guild with /rand loot, I suggest you look for one with membership mostly 20-30 in level. Many guilds have different memberships, leadership, and temperment. Some are hardcore and raid from noon to 7(or 9)am then sleep for 4 hours and do it over again. Find a good one - not necessarily the best - you do not need to be in FOH to have fun in eq.</p>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
